captions.text: -Hello, guys!

It's Brooklyn and
Bailey, and today we're

going to be you
three lip tutorials,

because Valentine's Day is
right around the corner.

-These lip tutorials can be
used any other day of the year
as well.

And also, if you don't want
to miss any other our videos,

be sure to click the
Subscribe button right here,

somewhere on this screen,
not sure where it'll be.

Be sure to click
that Subscribe button

if you want to see all
of our other videos.

-Before applying
any lipstick, there

are two tricks that
you an use in order

to keep the lipstick
lasting all day long.

So first, take a foundation,
preferably the one

that you use, and we're going
to put this on our lips.

And this helps take away the
color from your actual lips

and helps you see the true color
of the lipstick you are using.

And then next, you're going
to apply a layer of powder
on top of that.

And this helps solidify
it and takes away

any liquid feeling
from the foundation.

So now, I'm just going
to do exactly that.

Now that I have
primed my lips, I'm

going to show you guys
my first lip look, which
is a soft and natural look.

So to start off, we're going
to take a white lip liner,

and we're going to fill it in
underneath our Cupid's bow,

following through
to the bottom lip.

And we don't want to
do the white too dark,

because we are going over
it with another lipstick,

and we still want to
be able to blend in.

Now that I've
filled in my white,

I'm going to take my NYX Snow
Cap nude natural lipstick,

and I'm going to apply it
over the top of the white.

And as you can see, the white
line is tell pretty apparent,

so we're going to go
ahead and take our finger
and just blend it in.

Now that I have finished
applying my lipstick,

you can still see a little
bit of the white, which

helps make your lips
look a little bit fuller.

And I'm going to
apply my NYX Fair Lady

lip gloss over the top just
to give you a little bit more
of a shine to it.

And there you have the
soft, natural look.

-Today, I'm going to
be starting by showing

you guys an
AndreasChoice-inspired bold red
lip look.

And obviously, I've
already primed my lips,

so I'm just going to start
by applying this lip liner.

It's from Make Up
Forever, and it's 12C,

in case you guys
wanted to get it.

And I'm going to apply
lip liner around my lips.
I'm just going to trace my lips.

Now that you've
finished your lip liner,

you're going to start
applying your red lipstick.

And I have Rouge Artist
Intense by Make Up Forever.

But really, any dark
red color would work.

And I'm just going to apply
it inside the lip liner.
OK.

Now that you've done that, I'm
going to use a Sigma lip brush.

And this is the Lip-L05,
in case any of you
guys want to use this.

And I'm just going to
blend the dark lip liner
with my red lipstick.

And there you have
your bold red lip look.

As you can see, I have
finished priming my lips,

and now I'm going to show you
our very last lip look, which

we are calling the
perfect pink look.

So to start off, I'm going to
take my next lip liner, which

is called Citrine, and
I'm going to outline lips.

-Next, I'm going to
take my lipstick, which

is called Tea Rose,
by NYX, and I'm
going to go ahead and apply it.

I'm going to go ahead and take
my lip gloss, called Aqua Luxe,

by NYX, and I'm just going
to apply it on the top.

And this one I actually love,
because it's super-sparkly

and gives it a little
bit more pizazz,

since we are calling this
the perfect pink look.

And you have the
perfect pink lip look.

-I hope you guys enjoyed
our lip tutorial.

Be sure to leave a comment below
on which lip color or lip style
was your favorite.

And oh, my gosh, guys, we're
going to be at BeautyCon Dallas

March 14, so if
any of you guys are

interested in coming or seeing
us, all of the information

will be in the
description box below,

so be sure to check
that out, and we
will see you guys next week.
Bye!
-Eww, I can't stand pickles!

Do I have to put a
whole one of these in?
-Jump, Bailey, jump!
Good, Bailey!
Brooklyn, what's your name?
-Brooklyn.
-What's your last name?
-McKnight.
-How old are you?
-Two.

-How much older are
you than Bailey?
Say two minutes.
-Two minutes
